The paper focuses on predicting human motion in collaborative settings, which is a key area of research in robotics. The use of motion capture and inverse optimal control techniques suggests a focus on robotics and machine learning (cs.RO and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of human-robot interaction and collaboration, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of optimization techniques and machine learning also suggests a focus on algorithms and optimization (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
